gomodel:SYNGO_4179  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig2: APLP2 colocalises with dendritic marker MAP2 in primary cortical neurons; the colocalisation was abolished in APLP2 KO neurons indicating the specificity of the staining towards APLP2.\nFig4B: The endogenous localisation of APLP2 was difficult to discern due to the quality of the signal derived by the antibody. The paper used HA-tagged APLP2 and GFP to visualize the dendritic spines. Staining with anti-HA antibody revealed partial colocalisation with APLP2 in the head, neck, or at the bottom of dendritic spines.. Experimental description: C57BL/6J mice were used for the generation of primary cortical neuron cultures. The generation and genotyping of APLP2 KO was described in von Koch et al., 1997." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-18" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4179" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

